@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Pwaps" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries
are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must have at
least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on a tile that is surrounded by 4 other tiles; one at
left, one at right, one over and one under. Those tiles will swap their
positions as shown on the following illustration:

               a           b
                                 Note: the '*' symbol represents the
             c * d  -=>  d * c         clicked tile and the letters
                                       represent the tiles.
               b           a

  When tiles of the same type are placed next to each other, they are
then removed from the board. The number of points you get is calculated
according to the number of tiles that were removed, multiplied by that
number minus one. For example, if 6 tiles were removed, the number of
points will be 6 x (6-1) = 30 points.

  As tiles are removed from the board, they are replaced by new tiles.
The game continues until it is impossible to place tiles of the same
type next to each other...

  Have fun!

@endnode

